  "bio_raw": "Mainul Haque completed his M.Sc. degree in Electrical Engineering from Frederick University, Cyprus, under the Erasmus Mundus LEADERS scholarship program by the European Union, and his B.Sc. from United International University. Currently, he is working as a Senior Lecturer in the Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering at University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. Previously, he was a faculty member, program coordinator, and a member of the Outcome-Based Education (OBE) Committee, where he contributed to curriculum development and accreditation processes in the Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering at City University. He has more than eight years of experience in teaching and research. His research interests include artificial intelligence, VLSI, embedded systems, machine learning, nanotechnology, power systems, and optics.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Artificial Intelligence, VLSI, Embedded Systems, Machine Learning, Nanotechnology, Power System and Optics."
  ],
